article.description: Kyle Lofton had 14 points and 11 assists to lead Saint Bonaventure to a 75-50 win over Division II Gannon University on Saturday.
article.headline: Lofton leads St. Bonaventure over Gannon 75-50
article.linkText: Lofton leads St. Bonaventure over Gannon 75-50
article.story: ST. BONAVENTURE, N.Y. -- Kyle Lofton had 14 points and 11 assists to lead Saint Bonaventure to a 75-50 win over Division II Gannon University on Saturday. Justin Winston had 14 points for Saint Bonaventure (6-4), which earned its fifth consecutive win. Alejandro Vasquez added 12 points. Jaren English had 11 points and six rebounds for the home team. Benjamin Horsford had 12 points for the Golden Knights. Frank Webb Jr. added 12 points. Saint Bonaventure takes on Niagara at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
